elements.2211.03209_ca6fc37b5465b85806b56876e29ac: Inverter-dominated microgrids are quickly becoming a key building block of future power systems
elements.2211.03209_73030ca1565798df4fbe28ec46037: They rely on centralized controllers that can provide reliability and resiliency in extreme events
elements.2211.03209_088734752bb812f0583e096cb30f7: Nonetheless, communication failures due to cyber-physical attacks or natural disasters can make autonomous operation of islanded microgrids challenging
elements.2211.03209_81efc89329def4185d62e78feeaf9: This paper examines a unified decentralized secondary control scheme that is robust to inverter clock synchronization errors and can be seamlessly applied to grid-following or grid-forming control architectures
elements.2211.03209_9c89c1857320b9f30c0d0721801f9: The proposed scheme overcomes the well-known stability problem that arises from parallel operation of local integral controllers
elements.2211.03209_95fdd427b28ca3eb58448f77b6721: Theoretical guarantees for stability are provided along with criteria to appropriately tune the secondary control gains to achieve good frequency regulation performance while ensuring fair power sharing
elements.2211.03209_792e8deb29f73edca5f225e74d581: The efficacy of our approach in eliminating the steady-state frequency deviation is demonstrated through simulations on a 5-bus microgrid with four grid-forming inverters.
elements.2211.03209_e6763a503592d9ddcb6d846f2fe8f: Microgrids (MG) consist of a group of interconnected distributed energy resources and loads that act as a single controllable entity
elements.2211.03209_5152c400707fc6e85bb3995e999ca: Since MGs can operate in grid-connected or islanded modes they are touted as the key building blocks of future power systems
elements.2211.03209_d9e6a86cd98d614eac48b747685a9: Inverter-based MGs are attracting attention in industry and academia as they can improve reliability and ensure support for critical services even during extreme events
elements.2211.03209_333a8dc44f2fe0286ce80e656ade4: Operation of MGs in islanded mode is considered challenging as the dynamics of the MG are no longer dominated by the main grid
elements.2211.03209_96938177be4e2175b83a41a6a2780: In such scenarios, advanced control mechanisms are needed to maintain the delicate demand-supply balance
elements.2211.03209_a0c60e8ebc9f987ea3b84cf11116b: Hierarchical control schemes have been well-explored for operation of inverter-dominated microgrids
elements.2211.03209_b06306054c3e066475827aa70a64a: These schemes are classified into three levels of control that serve different functions:
elements.2211.03209_654371b04cbef20c64db3ad4da9ec: the primary control layer is the fastest and establishes power sharing;
elements.2211.03209_1e2454c3dbc41a5788dbd0604ec6f: the secondary control layer is responsible for providing frequency regulation and eliminating steady-state frequency deviations introduced by the primary control; and
elements.2211.03209_21d22b23a11866e10a99a75dabaf9: the tertiary control layer is concerned with defining the the long-term set points based on economic dispatch
elements.2211.03209_17167d2968b87f0d17ed1a771d00f: The primary control layer is largely droop-based and relies purely on local measurements
elements.2211.03209_52a9d3be70b48f1e916c16359058e: However, the secondary and tertiary control layers typically depend on communication
elements.2211.03209_02872af510ff0212e005d34659057: While centralized control architectures for secondary control provide good performance they are neither scalable nor robust to cyber-physical attacks
elements.2211.03209_4ef71675c08259bd04de5cc4db3c1: For this reason, a variety of distributed and decentralized secondary control (DSC) schemes have been explored; see
elements.2211.03209_26d57787e146abe8da8d1461ee4a2: Despite their many benefits, communication-free control schemes in MGs can lead to poor performance and instability if the inverter digital processor clocks used to generate the time signals are not synchronized
elements.2211.03209_464f979fab20a49c866c4b948aa19: The impact of clock synchronization on frequency regulation and power sharing has been briefly reviewed in literature
elements.2211.03209_dea6a32913fc8edfa6f8534a02e0b: Nonetheless, there is no unified and robust DSC scheme that can be implemented in both Grid-forming (GFM) and Grid-following (GFL) inverters
elements.2211.03209_3132e194726fd1da2c66bbe573c8d: Moreover, little thought is given on how to tune the secondary controller gains
elements.2211.03209_d5c5fda1925aef01e7d78cce4353a: In this paper, we address both these challenges.
elements.2211.03209_81fbf4150a43d67bc98b05505dcc1: we provide a unified modeling framework for investigating DSC schemes for both GFM and GFL inverters
elements.2211.03209_b7906361ce67de7b5da6f2daf896a: We also show that an adhoc DSC approach based on local integral controllers is not robust to clock synchronization errors
elements.2211.03209_035cb543bad261bc6e6a063a51076: Moreover, a novel DSC scheme with damping is proposed that overcomes these challenges
elements.2211.03209_2f0ac4913e2d89821e021e7230d77: Second, we provide stability guarantees for our proposed DSC scheme with damping in Section
elements.2211.03209_d9190826626c1c87544523277f6d0: We show that both the secondary controller dynamics and the MG frequency reach a steady state
elements.2211.03209_13bfb484ea6e2565a0254d94427ab: Further, based on the desired objectives conditions for appropriately choosing the secondary controller gains are also provided
elements.2211.03209_979f5e6810d4cc8a0cc74cbbb39b5: discusses simulation tests based on a 5-bus test case with four GFM inverters followed by conclusions and future research directions in Section

elements.2211.03209_ebe1536d18752ad89dc6c2bcb6d02: This paper introduced a decentralized secondary control scheme that is robust to clock synchronization errors and is able to restore the frequency in inverter-based islanded microgrids
elements.2211.03209_23eab669cc660ddd47b5cc61a7fb7: A unified control-theoretic approach was utilized to systematically show that the microgrid dynamics are stable and reach a steady-state
elements.2211.03209_684768afe1b6e5a1a3ca2bebd160e: The proposed DSC scheme is agnostic to the inverter-type and can be used seamlessly with GFM or GFL inverter architectures
elements.2211.03209_a3a908b9178bb57870c12d5abc3c1: Criteria for designing the secondary control gains such that they provide good performance for frequency regulation while ensuring fair power sharing are also discussed
elements.2211.03209_741151833f80e7adb03824cfba756: Current research efforts are focused on testing the novel DSC scheme under mixed setups of GFM and GFL inverters as well as validating the results in our microgrid hardware testbed comprised of several inverter-based resources.
